  <exercise label="variables-operators_exercises-ex-2">
    <statement>
      <p>The code declares an integer <pf>a</pf> and <pf>b</pf> and reads in a value for <pf>a</pf>. Later on, the code prints out the values of <pf>a</pf>, <pf>b</pf>, and <pf>c</pf>.</p>
      <p>Your task is to add code in between those parts that:
      <ul>
      <li>Sets b to have the value that was read in for a.</li>
      <li>Increases a by 10.</li>
      <li>Declares c and sets it to have the value of a (new value) plus b.</li>
      </ul>
      </p>
    </statement>
      <program interactive="activecode">
        <preamble>
<xi:include href="../../programs/variables-operators/exercises-0b.cpp" parse="text"/>
        </preamble>
        <code>

    //Your code here

        </code>
        <postamble>
    cout &lt;&lt; a &lt;&lt; " " &lt;&lt; b &lt;&lt; " " &lt;&lt; c &lt;&lt; endl;
}
        </postamble>
        <tests>
        <iotest>
          <input>5</input>
          <output>15 5 20</output>
        </iotest>
        <iotest>
          <input>6</input>
          <output>16 6 22</output>
        </iotest>
        <iotest>
          <input>0</input>
          <output>10 0 10</output>
        </iotest>
        <iotest>
          <input>-1</input>
          <output>9 -1 8</output>
        </iotest>
        </tests>
      </program>
  </exercise>


